PN,35202
SC,0002
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F352A1667777620
OL,5,FBut by 1972 the rule must have looked
OL,6,Fto some like the nanny state in action
OL,7,F protecting the public from the
OL,8,Fdangers of watching too much television
OL,9,Fand not knowing how to use the off
OL,10,Fswitch.
OL,12,FThe rule was scrapped in January 1972
OL,13,Fin part to compensate what was still
OL,14,Fthe ITA and the ITV companies for the
OL,15,Fdecision not to proceed at that point
OL,16,Fwith a fourth channel.
OL,18,FBut there was no significant change to
OL,19,Fthe schedules until the autumn.
OL,3,C50th anniversary of regular afternoon
OL,4,CTV
OL,22,                                   G2/8
