OL,5,FThe week before ITV unleashed a full
OL,6,Fafternoon schedule, the BBC quietly
OL,7,Flaunched Pebble Mill at One. The
OL,8,Fmagazine show ran for 14 years and was
OL,9,Fgreatly valued by its viewers.
OL,11,FEfforts were made to cheaply fill in
OL,12,Fgaps in the rest of the afternoon
OL,13,Fschedule but afternoon closedowns
OL,14,Fdidn't disappear entirely.
OL,16,FBy 1974 the BBC was trying to make a
OL,17,Ffew original mid-afternoon programmes
OL,18,Funtil disaster struck. Abandoning the
OL,19,Fafternoons back to the test card was
OL,20,Fone solution to a BBC cash crisis
OL,21,Fintensified by runaway inflation.
